:R-HSA-9603505  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_2001241 ;
        rdfs:comment        "When neuronal cells are deprived of the NTRK3 (TRKC) ligand NTF3 (NT-3), NTRK3 functions as a dependence receptor, promoting apoptosis. The pro-apoptotic activity of NTRK3 is implicated in proper nervous system development, by dictating the number of surviving sensory neurons (Tauszig-Delamasure et al. 2007). In the absence of its ligand, NTRK3 undergoes caspase-dependent cleavage (Tauszig-Delamasure et al. 2007), resulting in release of the NTRK3 killer fragment (KF). The NTRK3 KF, in complex with NELFB (COBRA1), inserts into the mitochondrial membrane, promoting cytochrome c release and apoptosome-mediated apoptosis (Ichim et al. 2013)." ;
        rdfs:label          "NTRK3 as a dependence receptor" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Orlic-Milacic, Marija, 2018-05-09" , "Authored: Orlic-Milacic, Marija, 2018-01-02" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Tsoulfas, Pantelis, 2018-05-09" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-9603505" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-9034015/R-HSA-9034015> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

